{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "worknest-api-collection",
    "name": "WorkNest API",
    "description": "WorkNest backend API — authentication, health checks, and more.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection and an environment file.\n2. Select **WorkNest Local** or **WorkNest Production** environment.\n3. Run requests in order: **Register → Verify Email → Login → Get Me**.\n\n## Cookies\nLogin sets an `accessToken` HTTP-only cookie. Postman stores it automatically — no manual token needed for `/me` and `/logout`.\n\n## Tokens from email\n- After **Register**, copy the token from the verification email into `verificationToken`.\n- After **Forgot Password**, copy the token into `resetToken`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:5000" },
    { "key": "testEmail", "value": "test.user@example.com" },
    { "key": "testPassword", "value": "TestPass123" },
    { "key": "verificationToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "resetToken", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "General",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Welcome",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [""]
            },
            "description": "Root endpoint — confirms API is running."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Health check used by Render deployment."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Full authentication flow. Recommended order:\n1. Register\n2. Verify Email (paste token from email)\n3. Login\n4. Get Me\n5. Logout",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.test('Registration successful', () => {",
                  "        const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "        pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    });",
                  "    console.log('Check your email for verification link. Copy the token into verificationToken variable.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"Test\",\n  \"lastName\": \"User\",\n  \"email\": \"{{testEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{testPassword}}\",\n  \"role\": \"client\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new account. Sends verification email.\n\n**Roles:** `client` or `freelancer`\n**Password:** 8–128 characters"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Email verified', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-email/{{verificationToken}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "verify-email", "{{verificationToken}}"]
            },
            "description": "Verify email using token from the registration email.\n\n1. Register a user\n2. Open verification email\n3. Copy token from URL: `.../verify-email/YOUR_TOKEN`\n4. Paste into `verificationToken` environment variable\n5. Run this request"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Login successful', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.user).to.be.an('object');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('accessToken cookie set', () => {",
                  "    const cookies = pm.cookies.toObject();",
                  "    pm.expect(cookies).to.have.property('accessToken');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{testEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{testPassword}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Log in with email and password.\n\nSets `accessToken` cookie automatically. Email must be verified first."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Me (current user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Authenticated', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.user.email).to.eql(pm.environment.get('testEmail'));",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the currently logged-in user.\n\n**Requires:** Login first (cookie sent automatically)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Logged out', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Clears the accessToken cookie."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Forgot Password",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Request accepted', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "console.log('If email exists, check inbox for reset link. Copy token into resetToken variable.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{testEmail}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "forgot-password"]
            },
            "description": "Request a password reset email. Always returns the same message (no user enumeration)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Reset Password",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Password reset', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"password\": \"NewPass123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password/{{resetToken}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "reset-password", "{{resetToken}}"]
            },
            "description": "Reset password using token from email.\n\n1. Run Forgot Password\n2. Copy token from email link: `.../reset-password/YOUR_TOKEN`\n3. Paste into `resetToken` variable\n4. Update password in body if needed"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth (v1 alias)",
      "description": "Same auth routes also available under /api/v1/auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register (v1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"Test\",\n  \"lastName\": \"User\",\n  \"email\": \"{{testEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{testPassword}}\",\n  \"role\": \"freelancer\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (v1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{testEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{testPassword}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Me (v1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "me"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
